## CONTAINER LOG VERIFICATION — PROTOCOL

**Every time a container is restarted, rebuilt, or changed:**

```bash
# Standard log read
docker compose -f waas/docker-compose.yml logs CONTAINER --tail=80 --no-log-prefix 2>&1

# Error scan (run separately — does not replace full log read)
docker compose -f waas/docker-compose.yml logs CONTAINER --tail=80 2>&1 \
  | grep -iE "error|critical|traceback|exception|fatal|failed|refused|cannot"

# Follow logs in real time (use when container takes time to initialize)
docker compose -f waas/docker-compose.yml logs CONTAINER --follow --tail=20 &
sleep 15 && kill %1
```

**Log approval criteria:**
- api   : no Traceback, no ERROR, no CRITICAL. Must contain "Uvicorn running" or "Application startup complete".
- admin : no "Failed to compile", no "Cannot find module", no "error TS". Must contain "Ready" or "started server".
- Any other container: no lines at ERROR or CRITICAL level.

**If logs indicate an error:**
1. Read the full traceback
2. Identify the file and line number
3. Fix the issue
4. Rebuild + restart + re-read logs
5. Repeat until logs are clean

